.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known from a large area of the Pacific coastal East Palaearctic, from the 
<collectingRegion box="[1240,1344,260,285]" country="Russia" name="Magadan" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Magadan</collectingRegion>
area of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,226,297,322]" name="Russia" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Russia</collectingCountry>
south into the Korean Peninsula. New for 
<collectingCountry box="[704,844,297,322]" name="South Korea" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[860,944,297,322]" captionStart="FIGURES 38 – 40" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1192,1215]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,373,1162]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[152,1437,373,1162]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 38 – 40. Korean distribution of the genus Perlomyia Banks, 1906 — 38: P. martynovi (Zhiltzova, 1975); 39: P. secunda (Zapekina-Dulkeit, 1955); 40: P. smithae Nelson &amp; Hanson, 1973." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/818413/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
